      <h1>Who we are</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">
      <p><strong>Stack and Sleep</strong> is an independent review site covering sleep optimisation technology and biohacking tools. Every product we feature has been researched thoroughly. We earn affiliate commissions from some of the links on this site — but our editorial judgements are entirely our own.</p>

      <h2>Why we started this</h2>
      <p>The sleep and biohacking space has a problem: most review sites are either written by people who haven't used the products, or they rank products based on who pays the highest commission. We wanted something different — a site where the recommendations are based on what actually works.</p>

      <p><em>Replace this section with your personal story — why you got into sleep optimisation, what problem you were trying to solve, what products you've personally tested.</em></p>

      <h2>What we cover</h2>
      <p>We focus on four areas where the evidence is strong and the products are genuinely useful:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Sleep trackers</strong> — Oura Ring, Whoop, Garmin Venu, RingConn and others</li>
        <li><strong>Sleep supplements</strong> — magnesium, ashwagandha, glycine, L-theanine</li>
        <li><strong>Recovery tools</strong> — red light therapy, cold plunge, infrared saunas</li>
        <li><strong>Biohacking tools</strong> — CGM tracking, HRV monitoring, sleep environment optimisation</li>
      </ul>

      <p>We do not cover mattresses or pillows. That market is dominated by large media companies with deep budgets. We focus on the areas where an independent voice can actually add value.</p>

      <h2>Our review process</h2>
      <p>We research products thoroughly before recommending them. Where we've personally used a product, we say so and provide real data. Where we haven't, we rely on published research, verified user data, and expert sources. We never fabricate experience.</p>

      <p>See the full methodology on our <a href="/how-we-review/">How We Review</a> page.</p>

      <h2>Affiliate relationships</h2>
      <p>This site earns affiliate commissions from product links. We are members of the Amazon Associates programme, Impact.com, ShareASale, and several direct affiliate programmes. Full details at our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a> page.</p>

      <p>Earning commissions does not affect our editorial conclusions. If a product isn't worth buying, we say so — even if it pays a higher commission than the product we recommend instead.</p>

      <h2>No medical advice</h2>
      <p>Nothing on this site is medical advice. We review consumer products — we don't diagnose, treat, or advise on medical conditions. If you have a sleep disorder or health concern, speak to a qualified medical professional.</p>
    </div>
